==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sedulity
<hw>Se*du"li*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sedulitas</ets>. See <er>Sedulous</er>.]</ety> <def>The quality or
state of being sedulous; diligent and assiduous application; constant
attention; unremitting industry; sedulousness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The industrious bee, by his <qex>sedulity</qex> in summer, lives
in honey all the winter.</q> <rj><qau>Feltham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sedulous</ent>⟦br⟧
